
[1]sworn

   SWORN, pp. of swear. The officers of government are sworn to a faithful
   discharge of their duty.

   Sworn friends, is a phrase equivalent to determined, close or firm
   friends.

   I am sworn brother, sweet,

   To grim necessity.

          Sworn enemies, are determined or irreconcilable enemies.
